a change to damage shields in the latest patch that may be good news for tanks that have trouble holding aggro.<br>
<br>
In the past, damage and hate from damage shields was not attributed to anyone.  If a mob killed itself on a damage shield, no one would get exp for the kill.  Now apparently the damage (and presumeably the hate) from damage shields is attributed to the person wearing the damage shield.  Theoretically, that 200 DPS damage shield you can get on raids with a bard in group will now be attributed to you, which I would think would be a huge amount of hate added to the MT.  <br>
<br>
The druids are mad because they can't powerlevel by tanking mobs themselves and just having the PL noob do 1 damage per mob, but if this is true I think it could have very large implications for aggro management in groups and on raids.  This is mostly unconfirmed, especially the part about hate, but it could be significant if it's true.<br>
